>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Money troubles </span><hr size=1> Problem: Out of Money =) <br>
I have been spending a lot of time just leveling as a Mage and have made it to 36 in a little less than 10 weeks or so but I need to find a place that I can solo and get some good loot.  This is my first char and I'm getting sick of everything in NFP being priced by the Kpp which is way outta my league at the moment hehe. Finally saved up 900pp and I want to keep working for some Tboots or a horse(the nedding while moving is too cool). So any suggestions on what to do for the most cash? I d really like to get a horse when I ding 40 or so... Thanks a lot <br>
<br>
Ethari <br>
Saryrn Server 36 mage  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=folicacidi>Folic Acid I</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(2/8/03 4:01:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Money troubles </span><hr size=1> I don't know if your care for a faction hit, but guards in HHK are good money. In about an hour and a half there at your lvl you could make a good 300pp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nagolxela>nagolxela</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 1:47:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Money troubles </span><hr size=1> or deputies in Misty Thicket.  I've recently made 200pp cash/loot in 1 hour killing deputies.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 12:01:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Money troubles </span><hr size=1> I kill the Paineel guards if I can find them when they're not camped; however, the newby guards are massive undercons so you need to get into the city itself, which means a few hours of slaughter in the Warrens for faction to get a key (unless, perhaps, you're an Erudite: don't know whether their faction is high enough by default) . Decent spawn time and 8-10pp per guard with NPC vendors and a bank right there, plus at 36 some of the guards in the first two sections of the city may still be dark blue for a bit of XP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 1:40:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Money troubles </span><hr size=1> Nope.  Erudites don't have the faction to get into Paineel by default.  I've killed everything that walks, crawls, hops, and flies in the warrens multiple times, and I am still dubious.<br>
<br>
If you can get to apprehensive, supposedly there is a quest with the necro at the entrance from TF.  He has lost his pet, and if you find it, kill it, and bring something back from it, you get a massive faction boost.  Enough to get a key. <br>
<br>
<br>
