<br>
Also, are the guards warriors or SK's? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 5:15:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Money troubles </span><hr size=1> I haven't killed them around the palace, but most of the guards up to that point in the city are certainly killable; just don't try the ones near the necro guild or you'll pull half a dozen red-con skellies from the nearby bar and die fast. All the guards I've killed are warriors, though on one occasion when my Necro was killing them someone had trained one of the SK trainers to a point near the guard in the SK guild, so they came too when I pulled the guard, so I had to FD... as a Mage I'd probably have had time to Gate while my pet valiantly died to protect me. Normally though, they're far enough away that pulling the guard from behind the door won't aggro them.<br>
<br>
To raise faction I just spent a few hours in the first room on the king side of the warrens when there were no lowbies killing for XP... my earth pet could kill many of the low-level mobs there in a couple of hits, and root any that tried to run. I was able to kill them just about as fast as they spawned, and made some money too with the bronze weapons they dropped.<br>
<br>
From what I remember, dubious to apprehensive was the slow, slow part (I think it's something like 600 kills); once I got to apprehensive I didn't take long to get to amiable so I could get a key. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailurya@themagicianstower>Ailurya</A> at: 2/10/03 5:18:23 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showPrevMessage?topicID=55.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showNextMessage?topicID=55.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.threadControl?topicID=55.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=55.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm44.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=55.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerf